    {
      "SurveyID": "SV_CLSBECREGROUP03",
      "Element": "SQ",
      "PrimaryAttribute": "QID12",
      "SecondaryAttribute": "",
      "TertiaryAttribute": null,
      "Payload": {
        "QuestionText": "<p><strong>[CONJOINT PLACEHOLDER — HIGH PRESSURE]</strong></p><p>Add a Qualtrics <strong>Conjoint</strong> question here per <code>qualtrics/blocks/05-rating-task.md</code> and <code>qualtrics/conjoint-spec.json</code>. Key settings:</p><ul><li><strong>Mode:</strong> Full-profile, rating</li><li><strong>Profiles per respondent:</strong> 12</li><li><strong>Rating scale:</strong> 1–7 Likert, anchors \"Not at all appealing\" / \"Extremely appealing\"</li><li><strong>Attributes:</strong> Format (Separate items, Bundle); Label (None, Menu Deal, Student Fuel); Composition (Sandwich + Water, Sandwich + Coffee, Sandwich + Coffee + Fruit); Price (3.50, 4.50, 5.50, 6.50); Pickup speed (Ready now, 2-minute wait); Packaging (Open tray, Closed container)</li><li><strong>Randomization:</strong> independent uniform per attribute; no-replacement within respondent</li><li><strong>Force response:</strong> ON per rating</li><li><strong>Back button:</strong> OFF (set in Block Options)</li></ul><p><strong>JavaScript to paste on the Conjoint question (Question JS):</strong></p><ul><li><code>qualtrics/javascript/timer-high-pressure.js</code> (loads only if pressure == high)</li><li><code>qualtrics/javascript/response-time.js</code> (always; writes rt_ms_{loopIndex})</li></ul>",
        "DataExportTag": "Q5a_placeholder",
        "QuestionType": "DB",
        "Selector": "TB",
        "Configuration": {
          "QuestionDescriptionOption": "UseText"
        },
        "QuestionDescription": "Q5a_placeholder",
        "Validation": {
          "Settings": {
            "ForceResponse": "OFF",
            "Type": "None"
          }
        },
        "Language": [],
        "QuestionID": "QID12",
        "QuestionText_Unsafe": "<p><strong>[CONJOINT PLACEHOLDER — HIGH PRESSURE]</strong></p><p>Add a Qualtrics <strong>Conjoint</strong> question here per <code>qualtrics/blocks/05-rating-task.md</code> and <code>qualtrics/conjoint-spec.json</code>. Key settings:</p><ul><li><strong>Mode:</strong> Full-profile, rating</li><li><strong>Profiles per respondent:</strong> 12</li><li><strong>Rating scale:</strong> 1–7 Likert, anchors \"Not at all appealing\" / \"Extremely appealing\"</li><li><strong>Attributes:</strong> Format (Separate items, Bundle); Label (None, Menu Deal, Student Fuel); Composition (Sandwich + Water, Sandwich + Coffee, Sandwich + Coffee + Fruit); Price (3.50, 4.50, 5.50, 6.50); Pickup speed (Ready now, 2-minute wait); Packaging (Open tray, Closed container)</li><li><strong>Randomization:</strong> independent uniform per attribute; no-replacement within respondent</li><li><strong>Force response:</strong> ON per rating</li><li><strong>Back button:</strong> OFF (set in Block Options)</li></ul><p><strong>JavaScript to paste on the Conjoint question (Question JS):</strong></p><ul><li><code>qualtrics/javascript/timer-high-pressure.js</code> (loads only if pressure == high)</li><li><code>qualtrics/javascript/response-time.js</code> (always; writes rt_ms_{loopIndex})</li></ul>"
      }
    },
    {
      "SurveyID": "SV_CLSBECREGROUP03",
      "Element": "SQ",
      "PrimaryAttribute": "QID13",
      "SecondaryAttribute": "",
      "TertiaryAttribute": null,
      "Payload": {
        "QuestionText": "<p><strong>[CONJOINT PLACEHOLDER — LOW PRESSURE]</strong></p><p>Add a Qualtrics <strong>Conjoint</strong> question here per <code>qualtrics/blocks/05-rating-task.md</code> and <code>qualtrics/conjoint-spec.json</code>. Same attribute/level matrix as 05a.</p><ul><li><strong>Mode:</strong> Full-profile, rating, 12 profiles, 1–7 scale</li><li><strong>No timer</strong> — this is the low-pressure branch.</li><li><strong>Force response:</strong> ON per rating</li><li><strong>Back button:</strong> OFF (set in Block Options)</li></ul><p><strong>JavaScript to paste on the Conjoint question (Question JS):</strong></p><ul><li><code>qualtrics/javascript/response-time.js</code> (always; writes rt_ms_{loopIndex})</li></ul>",
        "DataExportTag": "Q5b_placeholder",
        "QuestionType": "DB",
